    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Implement missing time_manager_iq_samples function for IQ sample timing\n\n### Summary\nThe IQ player module was missing the `time_manager_iq_samples()` function that is required for proper timing management of IQ samples during replay operations. When the IQ player attempted to process samples, it would call this non-existent function, resulting in undefined behavior and potential crashes during RF simulation.\n\nThe issue was traced to a missing time management module in `common/utils/` that should handle timestamp calculations for IQ samples. This fix implements the missing `time_manager_iq_samples` function along with supporting infrastructure including initialization, cleanup, and statistics tracking.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/time_manager/time_manager.c`: New implementation of time management functions for IQ samples including the missing `time_manager_iq_samples()` function\n- `common/utils/time_manager/time_manager.h`: Header file with function declarations\n- `radio/iqplayer/iqplayer_lib.c`: Integrated time manager initialization and calls to `time_manager_iq_samples()` in the IQ reading path\n- `common/utils/CMakeLists.txt`: Added time_manager subdirectory and linked the new library\n- `radio/COMMON/common_lib.h`: Added include for time_manager.h\n\n"
}